  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $s_t(n)$ be the $t$-smooth component of $n$ - that is, the product of all primes $p$ (with multiplicity) dividing $n$ such that $p<t$. Let $f(n,t)$ count the number of distinct possible values for $s_t(m)$ for $m\\in [n+1,n+t]$. Is it true that\\[f(n,t)\\gg t\\](uniformly, for all $t$ and $n$)?",
